.TH "DTC" "1" "" "KryoFlux 3.50" "User Commands"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
dtc - KryoFlux Disk Tool Console, floppy disk acquisition and conversion
tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]dtc\f[R] [\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]dtc\f[R] (Disk Tool Console) is the command-line component of the
KryoFlux software suite.
It controls the KryoFlux USB floppy controller board and provides
facilities to read, convert, store, and write the contents of legacy
floppy disk formats.
.PP
KryoFlux replaces a standard floppy disk controller and captures the raw
magnetic flux data stream from the disk surface, independently of the
disk\[cq]s encoding scheme.
Supported media include 3\[rq], 3.5\[rq], 5.25\[rq], and 8\[rq] disks
from a wide range of platforms: Acorn Electron, Apple, Amstrad CPC,
Archimedes, Atari 8-bit, Atari ST, BBC Micro, Commodore 64, Commodore
Amiga, MSX, IBM PC, PC-8801, Sam Coupé, ZX Spectrum, E-MU Emulator II,
and many others.
.PP
\f[B]dtc\f[R] can operate in two modes:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Hardware mode\f[R] (default): uses a connected KryoFlux board via
USB to read from or write to a physical floppy drive.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Image file mode\f[R] (\f[B]-m1\f[R]): operates on previously
captured KryoFlux STREAM files without requiring hardware (deviceless
mode).
All image conversion and analysis functions remain available.
.PP
A key feature of \f[B]dtc\f[R] is its ability to produce several output
image formats simultaneously in a single disk pass.
A raw STREAM file can be captured alongside a sector-decoded guide
format (e.g.\ AmigaDOS ADF): if the guide format signals decoding
errors, \f[B]dtc\f[R] automatically retries the track, ensuring both
verified raw data and decoded images in one operation.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Image and filename options
.TP
\f[B]-f\f[R]_name_
Set the output filename (without extension).
Wildcards are supported: \f[V]##\f[R] expands to a two-digit track
number, \f[V]#\f[R] to a single digit.
.TP
\f[B]-i\f[R]_type_
Set the image type.
May be repeated to produce multiple output formats in a single pass.
See \f[B]IMAGE TYPES\f[R] below.
Image-local options must appear \f[B]before\f[R] each \f[B]-i\f[R] they
apply to.
.TP
\f[B]-m\f[R]_id_
Set the device mode.
\f[B]1\f[R] = image file (deviceless), \f[B]2\f[R] = KryoFlux hardware
(default).
.SS Drive and hardware options
.TP
\f[B]-d\f[R]_id_
Select the floppy drive (default: 0).
.TP
\f[B]-dd\f[R]_val_
Set the drive density line.
\f[B]0\f[R] = Low density (default), \f[B]1\f[R] = High density.
.TP
\f[B]-a\f[R]_trk_
Set the physical position of track 0 on side 0/A (default: 0).
.TP
\f[B]-b\f[R]_trk_
Set the physical position of track 0 on side 1/B (default: 0).
.SS Track selection
.TP
\f[B]-s\f[R]_trk_
Set the start track (default: 0).
Image-local.
.TP
\f[B]-e\f[R]_trk_
Set the end track (default: 83).
Image-local.
.TP
\f[B]-g\f[R]_side_
Single-sided mode.
\f[B]0\f[R] = side 0, \f[B]1\f[R] = side 1, \f[B]2\f[R] = both
(default).
.TP
\f[B]-k\f[R]_step_
Track density.
\f[B]1\f[R] = 80-track / step 1 (default), \f[B]2\f[R] = 40-track / step
2.
.TP
\f[B]-ks\f[R]
Use only the explicitly selected tracks during analysis (default: auto).
.SS Sampling options
.TP
\f[B]-r\f[R]_rev_
Number of revolutions to sample per track (default: by image type).
.TP
\f[B]-t\f[R]_try_
Maximum number of retries per track, minimum 1 (default: 5).
.TP
\f[B]-tc\f[R]_try_
Number of retry cycles per track, minimum 1 (default: 2).
.TP
\f[B]-tm\f[R]_try_
Treat missing sectors as bad sectors.
\f[B]0\f[R] = off, \f[B]1\f[R] = on (default).
.TP
\f[B]-l\f[R]_mask_
Output verbosity level bitmask (default: 62).
Add values: 1 = device, 2 = read, 4 = cell, 8 = format, 16 = write, 32 =
verify, 64 = TI.
.TP
\f[B]-v\f[R]_rpm_
Target system drive speed in RPM (default: by image type).
Image-local.
.TP
\f[B]-x\f[R]_mode_
Extended cell band search (default: by image type).
Image-local.
\f[B]0\f[R] = image only, \f[B]1\f[R] = all, \f[B]2\f[R] = reference
only.
.TP
\f[B]-y\f[R]
Flippy disk mode: reverses the bitstream on the flip side.
Also used as \f[B]-wy\f[R] for write operations.
.SS Sector format options
.TP
\f[B]-z\f[R]_size_
Sector size.
\f[B]0\f[R] = 128 B, \f[B]1\f[R] = 256 B, \f[B]2\f[R] = 512 B (default),
\f[B]3\f[R] = 1024 B.
Image-local.
.TP
\f[B]-n\f[R]_scnt_
Sector count.
\f[B]0\f[R] = any (default), \f[B]+Z\f[R] = exactly Z, \f[B]-Z\f[R] = at
most |Z|.
Image-local.
.SS Output image options
.TP
\f[B]-oo\f[R]_ord_
Output image track order bitmask (default: by image type).
Image-local.
1 = side 0 descending, 2 = side 1 descending, 4 = side 1 first, 8 =
side-oriented.
.TP
\f[B]-os\f[R]_trk_
Output image start track (default: by image type).
Image-local.
.TP
\f[B]-oe\f[R]_trk_
Output image end track (default: by image type).
Image-local.
.TP
\f[B]-ot\f[R]_pct_
Data band threshold in percent (default: 30).
Image-local.
.TP
\f[B]-p\f[R]
Enable the Path Solver from this point in the command line.
.SS Calibration
.TP
\f[B]-c\f[R]_mode_
Calibration mode.
\f[B]1\f[R] = track read, \f[B]2\f[R] = maximum track, \f[B]3\f[R] = RPM
calibration.
.SS Write options
.TP
\f[B]-w\f[R]
Write image data to a physical disk.
.TP
\f[B]-wi\f[R]_type_
Source image type for writing (default: 0 = auto-detect).
.TP
\f[B]-wp\f[R]_par_
Platform-specific write parameter (default: 0).
.TP
\f[B]-wm\f[R]_mode_
Write mode bitmask (default: 0).
.TP
\f[B]-wv\f[R]_mode_
Write verification.
\f[B]0\f[R] = off, \f[B]1\f[R] = on (default).
.TP
\f[B]-we\f[R]_mode_
Erase mode (default: by bias).
\f[B]0\f[R] = normal, \f[B]1\f[R] = used sectors only, \f[B]2\f[R] =
full wipe.
.TP
\f[B]-wb\f[R]_bias_
Write bias (default: by image).
\f[B]0\f[R] = neutral, \f[B]1\f[R] = bias out, \f[B]2\f[R] = bias in.
.TP
\f[B]-wg\f[R]_side_
Unformatted side filter (default: 3 = both sides).
.TP
\f[B]-wk\f[R]_side_
Track crosstalk filter (default: 3 = both sides).
.TP
\f[B]-ww\f[R]_ns_
Write precompensation window in nanoseconds, max 10000 (default: auto).
.TP
\f[B]-wt\f[R]_ns_
Write precompensation time in nanoseconds, max 1000 (default: auto).
.TP
\f[B]-wo\f[R]_mode_
Save output stream to file during write.
\f[B]0\f[R] = off (default), \f[B]1\f[R] = on.
.SS Graph / plot options
.TP
\f[B]-pg\f[R]_type_
Graph type (default: 0).
\f[B]0\f[R] = none, \f[B]1\f[R] = sample, \f[B]2\f[R] = consistency,
\f[B]3\f[R] = path map.
.TP
\f[B]-pf\f[R]_mode_
Flip mode for graphs (default: 0).
\f[B]0\f[R] = off, \f[B]1\f[R] = side 1, \f[B]2\f[R] = both sides.
.TP
\f[B]-pw\f[R]_size_
Graph width in pixels (default: 800).
.TP
\f[B]-ph\f[R]_size_
Graph height in pixels (default: 600).
.TP
\f[B]-px\f[R]_fval_
Graph X origin (default: 0.0).
.TP
\f[B]-py\f[R]_fval_
Graph Y origin (default: 0.0).
.TP
\f[B]-pd\f[R]_fval_
Graph domain (default: entire track based on RPM).
.TP
\f[B]-pr\f[R]_fval_
Graph range (default: 0.000020).
.TP
\f[B]-pv\f[R]_rpm_
Target drive speed for graph rendering in RPM (default: 300).
.SS EDOS support
.TP
\f[B]-ec\f[R]
Add a catalogue/database filename for EDOS encryption key recovery.
.TP
\f[B]-ep\f[R]
Add an EDOS image file path.
.TP
\f[B]-ek\f[R]
Set the EDOS key output filename (default: \f[V]edos_key.txt\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]-er\f[R]_cnt_
Recover EDOS encryption keys (default: first key only; \f[B]-1\f[R] =
all).
.TP
\f[B]-ed\f[R]
Decrypt EDOS image header(s) to TXT format.
.TP
\f[B]-edc\f[R]
Decrypt EDOS image header(s) to CSV format.
