.SH PARAMETER ORDER
.PP
Certain options are \f[B]image-local\f[R] and must appear
\f[B]before\f[R] the \f[B]-i\f[R] option they apply to; they are
automatically reset after each \f[B]-i\f[R] is processed:
.RS
.PP
\f[B]-f\f[R], \f[B]-y\f[R], \f[B]-s\f[R], \f[B]-e\f[R], \f[B]-os\f[R],
\f[B]-oe\f[R], \f[B]-oo\f[R], \f[B]-g\f[R], \f[B]-z\f[R], \f[B]-n\f[R],
\f[B]-k\f[R], \f[B]-v\f[R], \f[B]-ot\f[R], \f[B]-x\f[R]
.RE
.PP
\f[B]Global\f[R] options affect all images regardless of their position
in the command line:
.RS
.PP
\f[B]-m\f[R], \f[B]-l\f[R], \f[B]-r\f[R], \f[B]-t\f[R],
\f[B]-a\f[R]/\f[B]-b\f[R], \f[B]-p\f[R], \f[B]-c\f[R]
.RE
.PP
\f[B]Correct:\f[R]
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dtc -ffilename.ext -v360 -z3 -i4
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
\f[B]Wrong\f[R] (image-local options after -i are ignored):
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dtc -ffilename.ext -i4 -v360 -z3
\f[R]
.fi
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Run drive calibration (maximum track detection):
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dtc -c2
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Dump an Amiga disk to KryoFlux STREAM files with AmigaDOS verification:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dtc -f/tmp/amiga/track -i0 -i5
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Dump a Commodore 64 disk to a G64 image with mastering information:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dtc -f/tmp/c64/track -i22a
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Dump an IBM PC 3.5\[rq] HD disk to an MFM sector image:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dtc -f/tmp/pc/disk -i4
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Convert STREAM files to AmigaDOS ADF without hardware (deviceless mode):
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dtc -m1 -f/tmp/amiga/track -fadiga.adf -i5
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Write an ADF image back to a physical Amiga disk:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dtc -f/tmp/amiga.adf -wi2 -w
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Generate a consistency graph from previously captured STREAM files:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dtc -m1 -f/tmp/amiga/track -pg2 -i0
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Dump a 5.25-inch 40-track DD disk (360 RPM):
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dtc -f/tmp/disk/track -v360 -k2 -i4
\f[R]
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[V]/usr/share/dtc/firmware_kf_usb_rosalie.bin\f[R]
KryoFlux firmware image, loaded to the board at each session start.
.TP
\f[V]/usr/lib/udev/rules.d/80-kryoflux.rules\f[R]
udev rules granting non-root access to the KryoFlux USB device.
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
